        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "perf(agents): cache provider tool schema normalization",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Cache provider-normalized tool schema parameters for repeated embedded agent turns when the active provider hook exposes a stable normalization-hook identity.\n- Keep the cache conservative and hook-owned: key includes the provider hook identity plus provider/model/API/base URL and ordered tool names with stable original schema signatures; values store only cloned `parameters`, never tool objects, execute closures, approval state, or guards.\n- Add `OPENCLAW_TOOL_SCHEMA_CACHE=0` as a kill switch, with cache-key, clone-safety, env-disable, and eviction coverage.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior addressed:** repeated embedded agent turns no longer redo provider tool-schema normalization when the provider hook identity, provider/model/config inputs, and ordered tool schema signature are unchanged. Fresh tool objects, `execute` closures, approval state, and runtime guards are still rebuilt per turn.\n- **Real environment tested:** local OpenClaw checkout at `/Users/guanbear/workspace/openclaw-5.4-src`, branch `tool-schema-cache-pr3`, head `a5874d8ac60cf2974b74cc66b50028db103b390e`, macOS host, Node 25.9.0 via repo `pnpm` tooling.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:** ran `pnpm exec tsx --input-type=module` locally with a script that imports `src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/tool-schema-runtime.ts`, uses the real bundled OpenAI provider hook path, recreates 50 representative OpenAI-style tool objects and fresh `execute` closures per iteration, then runs 100 normalization iterations with `OPENCLAW_TOOL_SCHEMA_CACHE=0` and 100 iterations with the default cache enabled. Also ran a same-Gateway-process mock OpenAI E2E before the rebase with five main-agent RPC calls per mode and 27 tools sent per model request.\n- **Evidence after fix:** current-head terminal output from the provider schema-normalization microbenchmark:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"head\": \"a5874d8ac60cf2974b74cc66b50028db103b390e\",\n  \"cases\": [\n    {\n      \"label\": \"cache-disabled\",\n      \"iterations\": 100,\n      \"toolCount\": 50,\n      \"ms\": 63625,\n      \"perIterationMs\": 636.25,\n      \"rssDeltaMb\": 447.7,\n      \"stats\": {\n        \"bypass\": 100,\n        \"hit\": 0,\n        \"miss\": 0,\n        \"store\": 0,\n        \"size\": 0\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"label\": \"cache-enabled\",\n      \"iterations\": 100,\n      \"toolCount\": 50,\n      \"ms\": 26927,\n      \"perIterationMs\": 269.27,\n      \"rssDeltaMb\": -3.1,\n      \"stats\": {\n        \"bypass\": 0,\n        \"hit\": 99,\n        \"miss\": 1,\n        \"store\": 1,\n        \"size\": 1\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nAdditional lightweight mock Gateway E2E evidence from the same PR code before the rebase:\n\n- cache enabled durations `[2105, 496, 471, 465, 470]`, p50 `471ms`, 5 model requests, 27 tools per request\n- cache disabled durations `[2002, 482, 472, 474, 470]`, p50 `474ms`, 5 model requests, 27 tools per request\n\n- **Observed result after fix:** the provider schema-normalization cache is active on the real bundled OpenAI provider hook path: the benchmark stores once, then records 99 cache hits while recreating tool objects and closures every iteration. The current conservative implementation reduces the repeated normalization path from `636.25ms` to `269.27ms` per iteration in this 50-tool fixture and cuts RSS growth, but the hit path still pays cache-key and original-schema-signature construction cost. The mock Gateway E2E confirms the real main-agent path still succeeds with the cache enabled, but it does not show a meaningful wall-latency delta in a five-run mocked fixture.\n- **What was not tested:** full live-provider end-to-end agent reply latency was not tested. This PR caches only provider-normalized schema `parameters`; it does not cache full tool inventory/materialization, prompt-report inputs, `core-plugin-tools`, policy resolution, or complete agent-turn startup. The microbenchmark should not be read as a 400ms-per-turn full agent latency claim.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm test src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/tool-schema-runtime.test.ts src/agents/runtime-plan/tools.test.ts`\n- `pnpm plugin-sdk:api:check`\n- Current-head scoped `pnpm exec tsx` provider schema-normalization microbenchmark described above\n- `git diff --check`\n",
        "branch": "tool-schema-cache-pr3",
